text: So what's interesting here, and then you can, you can make all sorts of other things clearly clear Complexity doesn't hurt that it's kind of organic looking as well But what's interesting about it is that it does not have, at least to my knowledge, I'm not a mathematician, but to my knowledge it does not have an explanation in physics It does not have an explanation of history It was not evolved, it was not selected Is, it is in some way indexed into by this tiny little, little seed or pointer I don't, I don't think you can call it a compression for reasons we can, we can talk about
content_summary: The speaker discusses the complexity and organic nature of certain structures or phenomena that, to their knowledge, lack a clear explanation in physics or history. They also mention the concept of a 'seed' or 'pointer' that somehow indexes these phenomena, but reject the idea that this could be considered a form of compression.
